##Core Concepts
​-In networking, if an IP Address represents a physical host, a Port represents a specific logical entry point for a service.
​-Total Port Range: 0 to 65535.
​-Privileged/Well-Known Ports (0–1023): Reserved for core system services (requires root/sudo access to open).
​-Registered/User Ports (1024–49151): Used for specific applications (like databases or web development).
​
# The "Golden Four" Standard Ports
​As an industry standard, the following ports are essential for infrastructure management:
Port   Protocol            Purpose Description
22       SSH          Secure Shell Remote server administration and command-line access.
80       HTTP         Hypertext Transfer Unencrypted web traffic (Standard).
443      HTTPS        HTTP Secure Encrypted web traffic using SSL/TLS certificates.
3306     MySQL        Database Communication
